{"id":"project-LICHEN-ezna","title":"Inconsistent settings rollback behavior on enqueue failure","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshcore/adapter.c
Line: 593-606 (commit_settings_with_ok)

When enqueue_ok fails after successfully persisting settings, the rollback behavior differs:
```c
ret = enqueue_ok(adapter);
if (ret < 0) {
    if (adapter->ops.persist_settings == NULL) {
        *settings = *old_settings;  // Rollback in-memory
    }
    // No rollback when persist_settings != NULL
}
```

The inconsistency:
- If persist_settings is NULL: enqueue failure rolls back in-memory settings
- If persist_settings is not NULL: enqueue failure leaves in-memory settings changed (matching persisted state)

This means the observable behavior differs based on whether persistence is configured, which is confusing.

